Notes for building on various platforms


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
generic POSIX:

Status:
Outputs to:
    - file descriptor
    - SDL
Ncurses is "RSN".

Recommended way to build:
make


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Kobo:

Status:
Cross-compiles and outputs to file descriptor.  E-ink display is "RSN".

Setup:
Get the dev tools:
    http://blog.ringerc.id.au/2011/01/preparing-development-environment-for.html
Get source from KoboLabs:
    https://github.com/kobolabs/Kobo-Reader
Make some links from within OcherBook:
$ cd OcherBook
$ ln -s ..blah../kobo/arm-2010q1/
$ ln -s ..blah../KoboLabs/hw/imx508/ntx/linux-2.6.35.3/include/linux/

Recommended way to build:
# Until e-ink fb is better, prefer fd:
OCHER_UI_FD=1 OCHER_UI_MX50=0 TARGET=kobo make


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Windows:

Status:
Builds under Cygwin as a POSIX app.
May someday think about WIN32 proper, perhaps via SDL.

Recommended way to build:
make


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Mac:

Status:
Untested; probably works with fd.


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
FreeBSD:

Status:
Untested; probably works with fd.


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Haiku:

Status:
Currently only outputs via fd.  Plan to output native too.

Current recommended way to build:
TARGET=haiku make

